
**Post 1**

URL: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/brendanhufford_heres-a-5-step-seo-strategy-so-absurdly-activity-7442917552370020352-MoeM

Content:
Here’s a 5-step SEO strategy so absurdly simple it feels wrong:

Find what your audience is already searching for
Create content that actually answers it
Make it ridiculously clear and useful
Distribute it where your audience already spends time
Repeat what works

That’s it.

No hacks.
No loopholes.

Just doing the obvious — better than everyone else.

The problem?

Most teams overcomplicate SEO.

They chase tactics instead of solving problems.

But the brands winning right now aren’t doing more.

They’re doing the basics — consistently.

**Post 2**

URL: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/brendanhufford_how-does-a-b2b-saas-company-double-their-activity-7445447453736144897-s9rG

Content:
How does a B2B SaaS company double their pipeline?

Not by creating more content.

But by creating better content for the right stage.

Most companies focus only on top-of-funnel:

Blogs
SEO traffic
Awareness

But pipeline comes from:

Middle-of-funnel education
Bottom-of-funnel proof

What actually works:
→ Clear problem definition
→ Actionable frameworks
→ Real case studies

Because traffic doesn’t equal revenue.

Content that moves buyers forward does.

**Post 3**

URL: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/brendanhufford_most-seo-and-aeo-pages-convert-like-garbage-activity-7442193777181708288-U3jO

Content:
Most SEO (and AEO) pages convert like garbage.

Why?

Because they’re built to rank — not convert.

They:

Answer the question
But don’t move the buyer forward

So what’s missing?

→ Clear next steps
→ Strong positioning
→ Conversion intent

If your page doesn’t guide the user after the answer,

…it’s just a dead end.

And dead ends don’t drive revenue.

**Post 4**

URL: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/brendanhufford_an-hr-tech-company-former-client-thought-activity-7439657023157313536-mulB

Content:
An HR tech company (former client) thought SEO was their problem.

It wasn’t.

They had traffic.

What they didn’t have was:

Clear messaging
Strong positioning
Content that actually converted

So we didn’t focus on more traffic.

We fixed:
→ What the page said
→ Who it was for
→ Why it mattered

And that’s what changed results.

Because most growth problems aren’t traffic problems.

They’re clarity problems.
